
On most days, Michael White rises at 5 a.m. and starts checking his e-mail and the Internet for news of death in Iraq. Have U.S. or other coalition troops been killed overnight? Iraqi police? Civilians? If there's sad news to report, the Stone Mountain man updates his Web site &mdash; icasualties.org &mdash; before leaving for his paying job as a software engineer in Alpharetta. 

